Load data

data_folder <- "/Users/wrobelj/Data/2022/PupilLightReflex/" 

# load trajectories at post event
post <- readRDS(here::here(data_folder, "PupilLightReflex_POST_rightEye_20221208.rds")) %>% 
  select(user_cat = user_cat.x, subject_id, frame, percent_change)

Function to process data for use in GAM and refund models

process_sofr = function(df, last_frame = 400){
  sofr_df = df %>%
    filter(frame <= last_frame) %>%
    mutate(smoker = ifelse(user_cat %in% c("occasional", "daily"), 1, 0)) %>%
    select(subject_id, smoker, frame, percent_change) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = frame, values_from = percent_change, 
                names_prefix = "frame_")

    pupil_mat = sofr_df %>% select(starts_with("frame")) %>% as.matrix()

# reorganize data for use with refund::pfr() function
  sofr_df = sofr_df %>%
    select(-starts_with("frame")) %>%
    mutate(percent_change = I(pupil_mat))
  
  ncols = ncol(pupil_mat)

  sind <- seq(0, 1, len = ncols)
  smat <- matrix(sind, nrow(sofr_df), ncols, byrow = TRUE)

  #sofr_df$Zraw <- I(as.matrix(sofr_right_post))
  sofr_df$smat <- I(smat)
  sofr_df$lmat <- I(matrix(1/ncols, nrow(sofr_df), ncols))
  sofr_df$zlmat <- I(sofr_df$lmat * sofr_df$percent_change)
  
  sofr_df

}

GAM appoach

With 400 frames (includes lots of zeros at the tail)

df_400 = process_sofr(post, last_frame = 400)

gam_mod_400 <- gam(smoker ~ s(smat, by=zlmat, bs = "cr", k = 30), 
                   data= df_400,
                   method = "REML", family = binomial)
summary(gam_mod_400)
## 
## Family: binomial 
## Link function: logit 
## 
## Formula:
## smoker ~ s(smat, by = zlmat, bs = "cr", k = 30)
## 
## Parametric coefficients:
##             Estimate Std. Error z value Pr(>|z|)
## (Intercept)   0.9073     0.7066   1.284    0.199
## 
## Approximate significance of smooth terms:
##                edf Ref.df Chi.sq p-value
## s(smat):zlmat 2.57  2.903  2.645   0.382
## 
## R-sq.(adj) =  0.0296   Deviance explained = 5.69%
## -REML = 34.945  Scale est. = 1         n = 53
roc_in_sample <- roc(gam_mod_400$model$smoker, gam_mod_400$fitted.values)
auc(roc_in_sample)
## Area under the curve: 0.6565

Constructing plot

df_sofr <- data.frame("smat" = seq(0, 1, length.out = ncol(df_400$percent_change)),
                      "zlmat" = 1)
sofr_pred <- predict(gam_mod_400, newdata = df_sofr, , se.fit = TRUE, type = "iterms")
plot.sofr <- data.frame("frame" = 0:(ncol(df_400$percent_change) - 1),
                            "f0" = sofr_pred$fit[, 1],
                            'f0.se' = sofr_pred$se.fit[, 1])

p400 = ggplot(data = plot.sofr, aes(x=frame, y = exp(f0)))+
  geom_line()+
  geom_line(aes(x=frame, y = exp(f0-2*f0.se)), linetype = 'longdash')+
  geom_line(aes(x=frame, y = exp(f0+2*f0.se)), linetype = 'longdash')+
  geom_hline(yintercept = 1, color = "red", linetype = 3) +
  ylim(0,10) +
  labs(title = "Odd Ratio of being smoker vs. non, 400 frames")+
  theme_bw()

Explanation?

I suspect this is just a sample size issue since you lose 25 more subjects when you have the higher number of frames.

df_400[complete.cases(df_400),] %>% nrow()
## [1] 53
df_350[complete.cases(df_350),] %>% nrow()
## [1] 79

If I rerun the analysis using data that carried the last value forward such that no subjects are missing values, the results are as follows:

# use last observation carried forward for subjects with "NA" at the end 
post_imputed = post %>%
  group_by(subject_id) %>%
  mutate(last_frame = ifelse(any(is.na(percent_change)), min(frame[which(is.na(percent_change))])-1,
                             max(frame)),
         last_pctChange = percent_change[which(frame == last_frame)]) %>%
  ungroup()  %>%
  mutate(percent_change = ifelse(is.na(percent_change), last_pctChange, percent_change))

df_imputed = process_sofr(post_imputed, last_frame = 400)

Run gam model
